TITLE: Building Initial Environment in Crossplane Compositions
DESCRIPTION: A simplified implementation showing how Crossplane builds the initial in-memory environment from a composition. It starts with default data and merges in data from any selected EnvironmentConfigs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/crossplane/crossplane/blob/main/design/one-pager-composition-environment-beta.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// simplified logic implemented by the composite.APIEnvironmentFetcher
func buildInitialEnvironment(composition) (env environment) {
  // start from the defaults, if any
	env := composition.spec.environment.defaultData

	// get all the EnvironmentConfigs selected by the composition, either by name or via label selectors
	for _, envConfig = range composition.GetSelectedEnvironmentConfigs() {
		env = merge(env, envConfig.data)
	}

	return env
}
```

