TITLE: Properly Scoped Error Handling Pattern
DESCRIPTION: Recommended approach to error handling with errors scoped to their conditional blocks to prevent shadowing issues.
SOURCE: https://github.com/crossplane/crossplane/blob/main/contributing/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func example() error {
        if err := enable(); err != nil {
                // 'err' exists here inside the conditional block.
                return errors.Wrap(err, "could not enable the thing")
        }

        // 'err' does not exist here at the function scope. It's scoped to the
        // above conditional block.

        return errors.Wrap(emit(), "could not emit the thing")
}
```

