TITLE: Non-Scoped Error Handling Pattern (Anti-pattern)
DESCRIPTION: Example showing a non-recommended approach to error handling where the error variable is scoped to the function level, which can lead to shadowing issues.
SOURCE: https://github.com/crossplane/crossplane/blob/main/contributing/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func example() error {
        err := enable()
        if err != nil {
                return errors.Wrap(err, "could not enable the thing")
        }

        // 'err' still exists here at the function scope.

        return errors.Wrap(emit(), "could not emit the thing")
}
```

